A BMP receptor type-1A isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs within the GS-motif by BMP receptor type-2 upon BMP ligand binding.

label.value: DNA-binding protein inhibitor ID-2 isoform 1 phosphorylated 1

value.value: A DNA-binding protein inhibitor ID-2 isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs at the Ser residue in the N-terminal SPVR motif. Example: UniProtKB:Q02363-1, Ser-5, MOD:00046.

label.value: DNA-binding protein inhibitor ID-3 isoform 1 phosphorylated 1

value.value: A DNA-binding protein inhibitor ID-3 isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs at the Ser residue in the N-terminal SPVR motif. Example: UniProtKB:Q02535-1, Ser-5, MOD:00046.

label.value: DNA-binding protein inhibitor ID-3 isoform 1 ubiquitinated 1

value.value: A DNA-binding protein inhibitor ID-3 isoform 1 ubiquitinated form that has been ubiquitinated by COP9 signalosome complex for degradation.
A RING-box protein 2 isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs at the most N-terminal Thr residue by CK2. Example: UniProtKB:Q9UBF6-1, Thr-10, MOD:00047.

label.value: TGF-beta receptor type-1 isoform 1, signal peptide removed form

value.value: A TGF-beta receptor type-1 isoform 1 that has had the signal peptide removed to yield the mature protein.

label.value: TGF-beta receptor type-1 isoform 1, signal peptide removed phosphorylated 1

value.value: A TGF-beta receptor type-1 isoform 1, signal peptide removed phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs within the GS-motif region (GSGSGLP and surrounding sequence) by TGFBR2. Phosphorylation of any of the Ser or Thr seems to be sufficient to transduce signal, however full activation is achieved when five of these residues are phosphorylated. Example: UniProtKB:P36897-1, 34-503, Ser-165/Ser-187/Ser-189/Ser-191, MOD:00046|Thr-185/Thr-186, MOD:00047.

label.value: activin receptor type-1 isoform 1, signal peptide removed phosphorylated 1

value.value: An activin receptor type-1 isoform 1, signal peptide removed phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs at Ser/Thr residues within the GS-motif region (GSGSGLP and surrounding sequence) by the activated activin receptor type-2 (PR:000000528 or PR:000000529).

An activin receptor type-1B isoform 1 phosphorylated form that is phosphorylated at Ser/Thr residues in the GS-motif region (GSGSGLP and surrounding sequence) by activated activin receptor type-2, and constitutes an active receptor subunit.

An activin receptor type-1B isoform 1 phosphorylated form that is phosphorylated on a Tyr residue within the protein kinase domain, as a result of platelet activation. Example: UniProtKB:P36896-1, Tyr-380, MOD:00048.
An activin receptor type-1C isoform 1 phosphorylated form that is phosphorylated at Ser/Thr residues in the GS-motif by activated activin receptor type-2, and constitutes an active receptor subunit.

label.value: activin receptor type-2A isoform 1 glycosylated and phosphorylated 1

value.value: An activin receptor type-2A isoform 1 glycosylated and phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs at Ser/Thr residues. This constitutes the active receptor subunit.

label.value: activin receptor type-2B isoform ActR-IIB2 N-glycosylated and phosphorylated 1

value.value: An activin receptor type-2B isoform ActR-IIB2 glycosylated and phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs at Ser/Thr residues within the GS-motif, and constitutes an active activin receptor subunit.

label.value: Muellerian-inhibiting factor isoform 1 cleaved and glycosylated 2

value.value: A Muellerian-inhibiting factor isoform 1 cleaved and glycosylated form that has been cleaved at the RxxR dibasic cleavage site rendering the propeptide and the mature protein non-covalently bound.

A c-myc protein isoform 1 acetylated form that has been acetylated at Lys residues by histone acetyltransferase p300. Example: UniProtKB:P01106-1, Lys-143/Lys-157/Lys-275/Lys-317/Lys-323/Lys-371, MOD:00394.

A c-myc protein isoform 1 glycosylated form that has been O-glycosylated at the Thr residue within the L[LY]PTLTPPLS sequence of the Myc box I within the amino-terminal regulatory domain. Example: UniProtKB:P01106-1, Thr-58, MOD:00806.

A c-myc protein isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs at the Ser residue within the L[LY]PTLTPPLS sequence of the Myc box I within the amino-terminal regulatory domain by ERK through activation of Raf signaling pathway. Example: UniProtKB:P01106-1, Ser-62, MOD:00046.

A c-myc protein isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs at the Ser and Thr residues within the L[LY]PTLTPPLS sequence of the Myc box I within the amino-terminal regulatory domain, by ERK and GSK3, respectively. Example: UniProtKB:P01106-1, Thr-58, MOD:00047|Ser-62, MOD:00046.

definition.value: Category=modification. Note: This form is not stable and is degraded through the proteosome pathway.
